                        <h1>December 15, 2008</h1>
                                                               
                        

Check out a whole host of first-timers who are getting their products ready for you — and for the 2009 International CES, January 8-11, 2009, in Las Vegas. And they’re not the only ones prepping. So are a host of Major League Baseball stars. <BR><BR>And if that’s not enough, we’re giving you 30 Days of Innovation: A Countdown to CES, featuring some of the hottest technology you’ll find on the show floor.


        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif"/><br />

<a name="2739"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Gaming, Digital Imaging and Location Based Services Among 300 New Exhibitors at CES</div>
<br />

<IMG height=125 hspace=8 src="/images/photos/p43.jpg" width=165 align=right vspace=5>Three hundred new first-time exhibitors are among the more than 2,700 exhibiting companies across a wide range of categories, including gaming, in-vehicle electronics, information technology, content and broadband service providers, unveiling new technology products at the 2009 International CES, the world’s largest consumer technology tradeshow. <BR><BR>The product categories of gaming, digital imaging, entertainment content and location based services (LBS) are growth leaders for the holiday sales season and on the 2009 CES showfloor.&nbsp;&nbsp; New exhibitors in 2009 include such marquee companies as Blockbuster, Chumby, Electronic Arts, Eye-Fi, Huawei, Hyundai/Kia, Mattel, ooma, Phoenix Technology, PricewaterhouseCoopers and Verizon Wireless. <BR><BR>CEA projects 5.6 percent growth for the gaming category this holiday season, 6.9 percent growth for digital imaging and 30 percent growth in holiday sales for GPS/LBS products, with an increased showing from exhibitors in these categories at the 2009 International CES.&nbsp; Overall, the 2009 CES will feature 2,700 exhibitors from 30 product categories across 1.7 million net square feet of space.<BR><BR>“The 2009 International CES momentum is strong,” said Gary Shapiro, president and CEO, CEA. “In this challenging economy, our industry knows that CES is more important than ever to grow business.&nbsp; With each CES attendee holding an average of 12 meetings at our tradeshow, there is no better strategy for generating leads and jumpstarting new business than attending the 2009 International CES. In tough economic times, tradeshows make the most business sense and CES is the must-attend event of the year for our industry.”<BR><BR><A href="/exhibitorDirectory/default.asp">See who’s exhibiting at the 2009 International CES. <BR></A>
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif"/><br />

<a name="2736"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">30 Days of Innovation: The Countdown to CES</div>
<br />

The International CES is about innovation. The most important technologies launched at CES, including the VCR, DVD player, HDTVand satellite radio. Why does the average U.S. household have 24 consumer electronics (CE) products? Because they improve our lives, and in times like these, making life good – especially in our homes – is more important than ever.<BR><BR>That's why this year we launched <A href="/news/30daysInnovation.asp">"30 Days of Innovation: The Countdown to CES,"</A> a window into the kind of technological innovation only found at CES. See 30 new CES exhibitors – a new one each day – from among more than 300 companies showing their innovation to CES attendees for the first time. But this is just the beginning. Imagine learning about next-gen technology from <A href="/exhibitorDirectory/default.asp">2,700 of the world’s leading companies</A> in one trip.<BR><BR>Here's a peek at the list from last week: 
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text>Day 30 - Chumby: Cuddly and Functional</LI>
<LI class=text>Day 29 - Hyperspace by Phoenix Technologies: Changing the Way People Use Laptops</LI>
<LI class=text>Day 28 - Eye-Fi: Automatic, Wireless Picture Uploads</LI>
<LI class=text>Day 27 - Mango Radio by Areaware - Wood you like to listen to this? We would!</LI>
<LI class=text>Day 26 - Powermat: Place Your Device On the Mat and Watch it Charge</LI>
<LI class=text>Day 25 - Alert GPS from GPS Prevent: No More Road Worries</LI></UL><BR><BR><A href="/news/30daysInnovation.asp">See who else made the list so far.</A>
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif"/><br />

<a name="2738"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Dr. Oz, Joba Chamberlain and Stevie Wonder Among Stars You’ll See at CES</div>
<br />

<A href="/events/celebrities.asp"><IMG height=175 hspace=8 src="/images/photos/DrOz_175x175t.jpg" width=175 align=right vspace=5 border=0>Legendary musicians, actors and sports icons </A>come together at the 2009 International CES to experience, promote and cover the hottest products and technologies in the consumer electronics industry. Major League Baseball stars including New York Yankees pitcher Joba Chamberlain and Boston Red Sox designated hitter David Ortiz will help promote Sharp Electronics, the official HD of MLB. Dr. Oz, known for his frequent appearances on The Oprah Winfrey Show, will appear at CES on behalf of Sony Pictures Television. And Stevie Wonder has his very own TechZone. <BR><BR>The list builds each week. <A href="/events/celebrities.asp">See the ever-growing list of celebrities planning to attend the 2009 CES.</A>&nbsp; 
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif"/><br />

<a name="2737"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Money-Saving Tip: $100 Off Global Media Awards™ Tickets</div>
<br />

In each issue of CES Up to the Minute, we give you at least one way to save money. Just call us your friendly bottom-line boosters. This time around, learn how you can attend the <A href="/awards/GMA.asp">Global Media Awards™</A> at CES for, while saving $100. <BR><BR><IMG height=138 hspace=8 src="/images/content/GlobalMediaAwardsCombo275.gif" width=275 align=right>Opening night at CES will feature the inaugural presentation of the <A href="/awards/GMA.asp">Global Media Awards</A>. The ceremony honors creative content and technology on this important occasion in the evolution of the communications industry. We launch with a special recognition of the chief executives of the leading mobile telephone manufacturers who have pioneered the future of digital communications and competitive digital content awards whose nominees include the leading creative networks, channels and agencies of CBS, NBC, FOX, BBC, Warner Brothers, You Tube, Sundance, Discovery, DIRECTV, BBDO, McCann Erikson, Bravo, MTV, Disney, The New York Times, Starz, Wieden + Kennedy, Ogilvy, ESPN, Sony, Turner, NASCAR, HSN and Scripps.&nbsp; <BR><BR>Networking cocktail reception at 6 p.m. with dinner and presentation at 7 p.m. <STRONG>There is a special rate of $400 for CES attendees.</STRONG> E-mail <A href="mailto:events@natasonline.com">events@natasonline.com</A> or call 212-484-9440 with any questions and to take advantage of the discount.<BR><BR>Categories for the <A href="/awards/GMA.asp">Global Media Awards</A> include short form, advertising, website/Internet, repurposed linear/traditional content, long form, platform and user experience/program guide.<BR><BR><A href="/awards/GMA.asp">View the list of nominees.</A> <BR>For ticket information, call 212-484-9440 or e-mail <A href="mailto:events@natasonline.com">events@natasonline.com</A><BR>
